# UI Development

## Apple Human Interface Guidelines
- ALWAYS follow Apple's HIG: https://developer.apple.com/design/human-interface-guidelines
- Single-window utility apps should quit when window closes
- Document-based apps should stay running with reopenable windows
- When in doubt, consult the official HIG documentation

## Icons and Symbols
- Use SF Symbols for icons
- Prefer system symbols over custom icons

## Accessibility
- Support dark mode and dynamic type
- Include accessibility labels and hints
- Support VoiceOver navigation
- Test with accessibility features enabled

## Layout
- Use SafeArea and GeometryReader for layout
- Handle all screen sizes and orientations
- Use LazyVStack/LazyHStack for large lists
- Implement proper loading and empty states

## Interaction
- Implement proper keyboard handling
- Use animations sparingly and purposefully
- Implement proper menu bar behavior and keyboard shortcuts (macOS)
